<h1>Choose Or Reset Your Password</h1>

<%= form_for @user, :url => password_reset_path(params[:id]) do |f| %>
  <div style="margin: 10px auto; padding: 10px 0px; border-top: 1px dotted #000000; border-bottom: 1px dotted #000000;">
    
    <div style="float:left; width:50%; padding:7px;">
      
      <p style="margin-bottom: 10px;">To choose a new password, or reset an existing one, enter it here twice:</p>
      
      <div class="field" style="float:left;">
        <div class="email-input-float"><%= f.password_field :password, :class => "input170", :placeholder => "Enter new password…" %></div>
        <div class="email-input-float" style="padding-top: 10px;"> + </div>
        <div class="email-input-float"><%= f.password_field :password_confirmation, :class => "input170", :placeholder => "Confirm new password…" %></div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
        <div style="margin-top:15px;"><button type="submit" class="blueformbutton">Save New Password</button></div>
      </div>
      
      <% if @user.errors.any? %>
        <div id="error_explanation">
          <h2>Ejem…just <%= pluralize(@user.errors.count, "problem") %> with that particular attempt…</h2>
          <ul>
            <% @user.errors.full_messages.each do |message| %>
              <li><%= message %></li>
            <% end %>
          </ul>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    
    </div>
    
    <div class="error-explainer"><h2>Safe, Secure, Easy-to-Remember Passwords…</h2>
      <p>They are actually easier to remember for humans, as well as more secure. 
      <a href="http://xkcd.com/936/">This cartoon</a> explains it well.
      And this <a href="http://rumkin.com/tools/password/passchk.php">password strength tool</a> shows you and explains a bit more.
      The upshot is that you get to choose a <strong>simple human pass phrase</strong> instead of a random and very confusing group of letters generated by a computer.
      </p>
      <p>Instead of struggling to remember "mR9LVrsZ$%", you can do:
      <br /><br />- "$400 Chorizo Is Expensive"
      <br />- "Rajoy is a 1st class #####!!"
      <br />- etc.
      </p>
      <h3>Your password:</h3>
      <p>
      - must be at least 11 characters long;
      <br />- must include at least one lowercase letter, one capital letter, one number, one of these symbols—@#$%&+=—and one space;
      <br />- you can do a pass phrase with multiple words and spaces;
      </p>
      <p>…and be as creative as you like.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="clear"></div>

<% end %>
<div class="clear"></div>